file.title: Kaitlyn’s Questions:
file.preview:
1. I'm able to get the values for the graph of a topic with a GET request with the below parameters:
"ajax=1&q=<insert-trend-here>&geo=US&date=now%201-d&cid=TIMESERIES_GRAPH_0&export=5" http://www.google.com/trends/fetchComponent
but it returns a large string of HTML with the chartData buried in the middle. Is there an easier way of querying for the interest chart data for a particular trend? A way that would just give us the data and not the full page of html?

2. When running many of these GET requests in a row, I reached a quota limit. Is there any way to circumvent that?
